The paper deals with algorithms for solving problems related to utility functions and economic indices theory, which are topics in game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of polynomial time algorithms suggests that the paper may also involve computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The mention of the collective axiom of revealed preference and weak separability property suggests that the paper may also involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
